1
00:00:00,081 --> 00:00:12,081
( Watch on www.kissasia.co, .be, .org, .net, .id, .xyz )

2
00:00:37,605 --> 00:00:40,215
[This drama is fictional and any similarity
with reality is purely coincidental.]

3
00:00:40,215 --> 00:00:42,538
[Production guidelines were followed
when filming children and animals.]

4
00:00:42,538 --> 00:00:44,613
[Episode 6]

5
00:00:49,805 --> 00:00:52,805
President, are you not feeling well?

6
00:00:55,805 --> 00:00:57,838
You are burning.

7
00:00:57,838 --> 00:01:01,138
If you feel dizzy, maybe lean on me?

8
00:01:10,638 --> 00:01:13,105
Manager Nah, don't pretend you don't notice.
You need to go and handle it.

9
00:01:13,105 --> 00:01:14,105
Yes, I understand.

10
00:01:14,105 --> 00:01:15,638
Also follow up on the feedback.

11
00:01:15,638 --> 00:01:16,838
Yes.

12
00:01:16,838 --> 00:01:18,405
Well, we're off work now. No more work talk.

13
00:01:18,405 --> 00:01:20,038
Oh, yes.

14
00:01:20,038 --> 00:01:21,038
Where are you going?

15
00:01:21,038 --> 00:01:22,772
- Home.
- Let's have dinner together.

16
00:01:22,772 --> 00:01:24,072
I'll pass.

17
00:01:24,072 --> 00:01:25,338
Ah, Team Leader.

18
00:01:25,338 --> 00:01:27,105
No, thank you.

19
00:01:34,572 --> 00:01:36,305
Boss.

20
00:01:38,772 --> 00:01:44,038
President, the door will open soon.
Just hang in there.

21
00:01:44,038 --> 00:01:46,117
It's almost time to get off work.

22
00:01:46,117 --> 00:01:48,421
What should I do?

23
00:01:48,421 --> 00:01:51,172
Jeez, I'm going crazy.

24
00:01:51,172 --> 00:01:53,205
Ah, seriously.

25
00:02:03,138 --> 00:02:06,272
[Under inspection]
What? What's that sound?

26
00:02:06,272 --> 00:02:08,638
Why? Why did it stop while descending?

27
00:02:08,638 --> 00:02:10,638
Well, did it break down?

28
00:02:10,638 --> 00:02:14,038
Could it be that it is overloaded?

29
00:02:19,105 --> 00:02:21,829
I got it, alright.

30
00:02:21,829 --> 00:02:23,372
Oh, hello.

31
00:02:23,372 --> 00:02:24,405
What brings you here?

32
00:02:24,405 --> 00:02:25,705
Thank you for your hard work.

33
00:02:25,705 --> 00:02:28,805
Here, have this while you work.
Just try some.

34
00:02:28,805 --> 00:02:31,338
This is really refreshing, you know.

35
00:02:31,338 --> 00:02:33,638
I came to check the working environment.

36
00:02:33,638 --> 00:02:35,805
Is there anything uncomfortable
while you work?

37
00:02:35,805 --> 00:02:38,205
Yes, you can have that while you continue.

38
00:02:38,205 --> 00:02:41,072
What? If they were inspecting it,
they should've told us first.

39
00:02:41,072 --> 00:02:43,672
I'll contact the management office.

40
00:02:48,338 --> 00:02:50,038
Yes, hello?

41
00:02:50,972 --> 00:02:52,672
What?

42
00:02:54,705 --> 00:02:56,472
Oh, yes.

43
00:02:56,472 --> 00:02:58,705
Yes, I understand. Yes.

44
00:03:00,172 --> 00:03:01,805
Well...

45
00:03:01,805 --> 00:03:03,472
They said we should take the stairs.

46
00:03:03,472 --> 00:03:05,505
The elevator is broken.

47
00:03:05,505 --> 00:03:07,072
Oh, jeez.

48
00:03:07,072 --> 00:03:08,072
But it's the 5th floor.

49
00:03:08,072 --> 00:03:10,213
- Ah, I'm wearing heels.
- This is too much.

50
00:03:11,138 --> 00:03:12,772
Uh, President.

51
00:03:12,772 --> 00:03:15,072
Don't pay attention to the noises outside.

52
00:03:15,072 --> 00:03:17,638
If you're anxious, your breathing speeds up.

53
00:03:17,638 --> 00:03:20,272
Try this with me.

54
00:03:20,272 --> 00:03:23,005
Inhale and exhale

55
00:03:23,005 --> 00:03:25,305
as if letting air out slowly.

56
00:03:34,172 --> 00:03:36,205
It's okay. You're doing well.

57
00:03:36,205 --> 00:03:40,872
Breathe in slowly and out.

58
00:04:11,272 --> 00:04:12,605
If it gets tough this time,

59
00:04:12,605 --> 00:04:14,072
will you let go of her hand again?

60
00:04:14,072 --> 00:04:15,805
Like last time?

61
00:04:17,238 --> 00:04:20,272
President, are you not feeling well?

62
00:04:26,438 --> 00:04:28,305
She must be disappointed.

63
00:04:28,305 --> 00:04:30,105
She must've been surprised.

64
00:04:38,072 --> 00:04:40,005
You've been waiting a long time, haven't you?

65
00:04:40,005 --> 00:04:42,338
Here, have some water.

66
00:04:43,138 --> 00:04:44,838
Thank you.

67
00:04:47,005 --> 00:04:49,838
But are you really okay?

68
00:04:49,838 --> 00:04:51,572
You should go to the hospital or something.

69
00:04:51,572 --> 00:04:53,838
No, I'm just a little tired.

70
00:04:53,838 --> 00:04:55,572
Oh, well...

71
00:04:55,572 --> 00:04:57,305
- About earlier...
- Well,

72
00:04:57,305 --> 00:04:58,605
are you hungry?

73
00:04:58,605 --> 00:05:01,238
Would you like to have dinner with me?

74
00:05:01,989 --> 00:05:03,365
[Sales Team Meeting Room]

75
00:05:08,837 --> 00:05:09,905
[Hui Won]

76
00:05:09,905 --> 00:05:10,972
Think carefully

77
00:05:10,972 --> 00:05:12,572
whether what you feel now
is love or friendship.

78
00:05:12,572 --> 00:05:15,138
I guess it's not friendship.

79
00:05:18,738 --> 00:05:22,533
Hui Won, are you free this week?

80
00:05:22,533 --> 00:05:25,381
[Hui Won, are you free this week?]

81
00:05:39,572 --> 00:05:41,472
Let's see.

82
00:05:41,472 --> 00:05:45,405
[How to confess to an old friend]

83
00:05:45,405 --> 00:05:47,238
In a relaxed, natural setting,

84
00:05:47,238 --> 00:05:48,572
as you talk as usual,

85
00:05:48,572 --> 00:05:52,472
and then slip out a bit of honest feeling.

86
00:05:55,045 --> 00:05:56,613
Jeez.

87
00:05:58,245 --> 00:06:00,972
What am I doing, seriously?

88
00:06:03,538 --> 00:06:05,438
Keep it simple.

89
00:06:05,438 --> 00:06:06,438
Let's do it by text.

90
00:06:06,438 --> 00:06:09,305
Hui Won, are you free this week?

91
00:06:10,638 --> 00:06:12,705
[Hui Won, are you free this week?]

92
00:06:13,572 --> 00:06:15,505
- Assistant Manager Cha.
- Yes.

93
00:06:15,505 --> 00:06:18,905
The meeting ended ages ago.
What are you still doing here?

94
00:06:18,905 --> 00:06:20,072
Are you sleeping here tonight?

95
00:06:20,072 --> 00:06:21,438
No, I was just about to leave.

96
00:06:21,438 --> 00:06:23,905
Right, you should sleep at home. Let's go.

97
00:06:23,905 --> 00:06:26,205
Yes.

98
00:06:26,205 --> 00:06:27,572
Ah, you're slow.

99
00:06:27,572 --> 00:06:29,305
Coming.

100
00:06:32,538 --> 00:06:33,538
Enjoy your meal.

101
00:06:33,538 --> 00:06:35,372
Thank you.

102
00:06:36,338 --> 00:06:38,905
Um, about earlier...

103
00:06:38,905 --> 00:06:40,905
This is a great restaurant
I discovered during college years.

104
00:06:40,905 --> 00:06:43,038
I come here whenever I need
to restore my energy.

105
00:06:43,038 --> 00:06:45,605
Try the broth. You'll be amazed.

106
00:06:45,605 --> 00:06:47,338
It melts away a day's fatigue, no,

107
00:06:47,338 --> 00:06:50,405
maybe even a month's worth.

108
00:06:51,493 --> 00:06:55,472
Jeez. This is my secret spot.
I don't tell just anyone about it.

109
00:06:55,472 --> 00:06:56,505
I'm being generous.

110
00:06:56,505 --> 00:07:00,472
President, since you had
a rough day, I'll share it with you.

111
00:07:00,472 --> 00:07:02,205
Please try it.

112
00:07:10,005 --> 00:07:11,705
How is it?

113
00:07:12,805 --> 00:07:14,105
- It's delicious.
- Right?

114
00:07:14,105 --> 00:07:17,472
I told you this place is a gem.

115
00:07:24,172 --> 00:07:28,038
When we went to the hop farm...

116
00:07:28,838 --> 00:07:34,205
That day when I got mad at you
because of the text my mom sent.

117
00:07:34,205 --> 00:07:36,338
It's just

118
00:07:36,338 --> 00:07:39,505
that day keeps weighing on my mind.

119
00:07:39,505 --> 00:07:43,005
I wasn't actually mad at you.

120
00:07:43,905 --> 00:07:46,405
You'd understand if you saw the text.

121
00:07:46,405 --> 00:07:49,105
A shameful secret
I never want anyone to know.

122
00:07:49,105 --> 00:07:53,372
That's just how it is between my mom and I.

123
00:07:53,372 --> 00:07:56,905
So I just wanted to run away.

124
00:07:56,905 --> 00:07:59,372
Even though I knew you'd misunderstand.

125
00:07:59,372 --> 00:08:02,438
It's still a difficult issue for me.

126
00:08:04,938 --> 00:08:08,105
So you don't need to explain

127
00:08:08,105 --> 00:08:09,938
about what happened earlier.

128
00:08:11,072 --> 00:08:14,038
Thank you, truly.

129
00:08:14,038 --> 00:08:16,805
I mean, no one's made of steel.

130
00:08:16,805 --> 00:08:19,105
You can always talk if you need to.

131
00:08:19,838 --> 00:08:23,005
It's not like leaning on someone
will wear you out.

132
00:08:23,005 --> 00:08:26,238
Maybe five minutes?

133
00:08:26,238 --> 00:08:28,538
I can spare that much.

134
00:08:30,938 --> 00:08:32,572
Then I'll enjoy this.

135
00:08:32,572 --> 00:08:34,305
Eat up.

136
00:08:52,172 --> 00:08:54,053
[Jang Hui Won]
You finished the whole bowl.

137
00:08:54,053 --> 00:08:57,372
You won't feel sick anymore. Sleep well.

138
00:09:02,501 --> 00:09:03,909
[Kang Du Jun]

139
00:09:07,813 --> 00:09:09,125
[Kang Du Jun]

140
00:09:11,938 --> 00:09:14,605
Did the samgyetang work magic?

141
00:09:14,605 --> 00:09:16,705
It really doesn't hurt.

142
00:09:23,572 --> 00:09:25,705
[Finding the Next Try Beer]
Looking for the second Try beer?

143
00:09:25,705 --> 00:09:27,872
Oh, a beer proposal contest?

144
00:09:27,872 --> 00:09:29,305
Looks like they're making
the next beer after Try.

145
00:09:29,305 --> 00:09:30,469
If your recipe wins,

146
00:09:30,469 --> 00:09:32,172
[Finding the Next Try Beer]
it'll come out under your name.

147
00:09:32,172 --> 00:09:33,205
Awesome!

148
00:09:33,205 --> 00:09:34,372
Besides that...

149
00:09:34,372 --> 00:09:35,589
[Submission guidelines]
they're even looking

150
00:09:35,589 --> 00:09:38,138
at marketing and branding ideas.

151
00:09:38,138 --> 00:09:40,205
Doesn't it require a whole team?

152
00:09:40,205 --> 00:09:41,272
That's intense.

153
00:09:41,272 --> 00:09:42,772
Whoa, seriously intense.

154
00:09:42,772 --> 00:09:44,838
[Finding the Next Try Beer]
Hey, want to try it together?

155
00:09:44,838 --> 00:09:46,072
You can handle marketing, right?

156
00:09:46,072 --> 00:09:48,605
- You develop the beer.
- Jang Hui Won's going to get busy again.

157
00:09:48,605 --> 00:09:50,372
Let's do this ourselves.

158
00:09:51,205 --> 00:09:52,505
We absolutely have to do it.

159
00:09:52,505 --> 00:09:54,672
- Hello.
- Hello.

160
00:09:54,672 --> 00:09:56,338
Did everyone see the contest news?

161
00:09:56,338 --> 00:09:57,705
- Contest?
- Yes.

162
00:09:57,705 --> 00:09:59,472
[Beer brand contest]
It's an in-house beer brand contest.

163
00:09:59,472 --> 00:10:02,085
[Finding the Next Try Beer]
They'll launch it under the winner's name.

164
00:10:02,085 --> 00:10:03,305
Oh.

165
00:10:03,305 --> 00:10:04,872
Kinda makes me greedy.

166
00:10:04,872 --> 00:10:07,572
Oh great! I'm going all in this time.

167
00:10:07,572 --> 00:10:10,038
Then how about we each
join separately this time?

168
00:10:10,038 --> 00:10:11,772
Good.

169
00:10:11,772 --> 00:10:13,838
Let's try. Wanna make a bet?

170
00:10:13,838 --> 00:10:14,872
- A bet?
- Sounds good.

171
00:10:14,872 --> 00:10:17,538
- Good.
- The winner will do something for us.

172
00:10:17,538 --> 00:10:19,272
What? Why's it so noisy this early?

173
00:10:19,272 --> 00:10:21,405
- Oh.
- Team Leader, do you want to join too?

174
00:10:21,405 --> 00:10:22,972
- Join what?
- We were just talking about the contest.

175
00:10:22,972 --> 00:10:24,372
Oh, the contest?

176
00:10:24,372 --> 00:10:27,572
Seems you're unaware of my achievements.

177
00:10:27,572 --> 00:10:32,238
That Hit beer that followed
Try beer? That was my idea.

178
00:10:33,372 --> 00:10:35,805
Of course, due to cost issues,
it's now a thing of the past.

179
00:10:35,805 --> 00:10:37,738
So you won through a contest back then too?

180
00:10:37,738 --> 00:10:39,238
Oh, it was back in my day.

181
00:10:39,238 --> 00:10:42,138
No contest. I pitched it
as an assistant manager.

182
00:10:42,138 --> 00:10:44,638
I handled everything from planning to launch.

183
00:10:44,638 --> 00:10:47,877
Bang Soon Yi! Bang Soon Yi!

184
00:10:47,877 --> 00:10:49,572
Bang Soon Yi!

185
00:10:49,572 --> 00:10:52,905
- Team Leader!
- Bang Soon Yi.

186
00:10:52,905 --> 00:10:55,538
- Manager Nah In Nam.
- Yes?

187
00:10:56,738 --> 00:10:58,572
Didn't I say not to call me by my full name?

188
00:10:58,572 --> 00:11:00,338
Oh, sorry.

189
00:11:00,338 --> 00:11:01,772
Anyway!

190
00:11:01,772 --> 00:11:03,772
What's our team's name?

191
00:11:03,772 --> 00:11:06,972
New Product Development Team!

192
00:11:06,972 --> 00:11:10,872
So should we let other teams
steal this chance?

193
00:11:10,872 --> 00:11:12,438
- No way!
- No way!

194
00:11:12,438 --> 00:11:14,138
New Product Development Team.

195
00:11:14,138 --> 00:11:16,472
First place! Let's go!

196
00:11:16,472 --> 00:11:18,838
Let's go!

197
00:11:21,157 --> 00:11:22,872
Whoa.

198
00:11:22,872 --> 00:11:24,772
Manager Jang, the prize is 10 million won!

199
00:11:24,772 --> 00:11:25,805
If we win, let's split it.

200
00:11:25,805 --> 00:11:27,172
But you wanted a bet earlier.

201
00:11:27,172 --> 00:11:28,938
No, I'm saying I'll give it to you.
So, are you in or not?

202
00:11:28,938 --> 00:11:30,738
- Really?
- Who'll you partner with?

203
00:11:30,738 --> 00:11:32,738
- Can we share?
- I'll team with Manager Jang.

204
00:11:38,205 --> 00:11:42,538
Madam, here's the profile
of Hwang Mi Ran you requested.

205
00:11:43,538 --> 00:11:45,872
Thank you.

206
00:11:45,872 --> 00:11:49,172
[Hwang Mi Ran]
Another blind date for Du Jun?

207
00:11:49,172 --> 00:11:50,872
I told you before.

208
00:11:50,872 --> 00:11:54,605
There's this lovely lady I met
at a massage place.

209
00:11:54,605 --> 00:11:58,372
You said that single room felt cramped,
so that's what it was for!

210
00:11:58,372 --> 00:12:01,138
You two only said a few words,

211
00:12:01,138 --> 00:12:04,105
so how did she move your heart?

212
00:12:04,105 --> 00:12:07,138
So, are you married?

213
00:12:07,138 --> 00:12:08,805
- Pardon?
- What's your religion?

214
00:12:08,805 --> 00:12:10,338
Not seeing anyone?

215
00:12:10,338 --> 00:12:11,972
What do your parents do?

216
00:12:11,972 --> 00:12:14,738
Well...

217
00:12:17,238 --> 00:12:20,405
I was too pushy, wasn't I?

218
00:12:20,405 --> 00:12:21,905
My son just works

219
00:12:21,905 --> 00:12:27,138
all the time and still isn't married,
so I worry about him.

220
00:12:27,138 --> 00:12:31,938
I'm truly happy after getting married.

221
00:12:31,938 --> 00:12:33,701
What was so great about it?

222
00:12:33,701 --> 00:12:35,138
Well...

223
00:12:35,138 --> 00:12:39,305
Nowadays, I spend
a lot of time alone like this.

224
00:12:39,305 --> 00:12:42,005
But it wasn't like this
when the kids were young.

225
00:12:42,005 --> 00:12:45,472
I'd chat about everything
with my husband after work.

226
00:12:45,472 --> 00:12:49,305
In summer, we'd go to the beach and swim.

227
00:12:49,305 --> 00:12:55,338
In winter, we'd warm our hands,
have snowball fights, and decorate trees.

228
00:12:55,972 --> 00:12:59,301
There was never a time I wasn't happy.

229
00:12:59,301 --> 00:13:00,738
Oh.

230
00:13:00,738 --> 00:13:02,597
I'm sorry.

231
00:13:02,597 --> 00:13:04,438
Oh, I'm being sentimental in my old age.

232
00:13:04,438 --> 00:13:07,072
Oh, not at all!

233
00:13:07,072 --> 00:13:09,038
I'm so envious.

234
00:13:09,038 --> 00:13:14,372
Just hearing this, I can tell you're
a wonderful wife and mother.

235
00:13:14,372 --> 00:13:17,438
I think the reason your husband
could comfortably talk about his day,

236
00:13:17,438 --> 00:13:21,472
and your children could laugh
and run around so freely,

237
00:13:21,472 --> 00:13:23,572
is that you created

238
00:13:23,572 --> 00:13:28,229
such a warm home.

239
00:13:28,229 --> 00:13:31,472
Oh my... I'm going to cry.

240
00:13:32,938 --> 00:13:36,572
My son probably doesn't know I feel this way.

241
00:13:36,572 --> 00:13:39,572
I'm sure your son knows.

242
00:13:39,572 --> 00:13:42,305
He just hasn't said it yet.

243
00:13:46,105 --> 00:13:47,338
There's something like that.

244
00:13:47,338 --> 00:13:48,598
How should I put it?

245
00:13:48,598 --> 00:13:50,405
A kind of soul and sensitivity

246
00:13:50,405 --> 00:13:53,438
that only women share.

247
00:13:53,438 --> 00:13:56,405
Anyway, I think she'd be great with Du Jun.

248
00:13:56,405 --> 00:13:58,338
Just pretend you don't know about this.

249
00:13:58,338 --> 00:14:00,133
I'll handle everything.

250
00:14:00,133 --> 00:14:01,905
Jeez.

251
00:14:01,905 --> 00:14:03,638
Okay.

252
00:14:08,672 --> 00:14:10,501
[Jang Hui Won]
You finished the whole bowl.

253
00:14:10,501 --> 00:14:13,272
You won't feel sick anymore. Sleep well.

254
00:14:19,172 --> 00:14:20,472
What are you doing?

255
00:14:20,472 --> 00:14:21,605
Nothing, it's nothing.

256
00:14:21,605 --> 00:14:22,872
Let's have porridge for lunch.

257
00:14:22,872 --> 00:14:24,305
You probably haven't eaten
anything since yesterday.

258
00:14:24,305 --> 00:14:25,838
- I did?
- You did?

259
00:14:25,838 --> 00:14:28,072
You probably just drank electrolyte drinks.

260
00:14:28,072 --> 00:14:29,505
I had samgyetang.

261
00:14:29,505 --> 00:14:30,905
Samgyetang?

262
00:14:30,905 --> 00:14:33,338
You won't even eat porridge
when sick, but samgyetang?

263
00:14:33,338 --> 00:14:34,772
Some famous place?

264
00:14:34,772 --> 00:14:36,572
There was a place like that.

265
00:14:36,572 --> 00:14:38,538
It felt like a really old,
legendary restaurant,

266
00:14:38,538 --> 00:14:40,772
and the walls were covered in graffiti...

267
00:14:44,101 --> 00:14:46,205
Oh, I should take this call. Be right back.

268
00:14:46,205 --> 00:14:47,938
Okay.

269
00:14:59,845 --> 00:15:01,157
[24.11.05, Came again, Min Uk and Hui Won]

270
00:15:02,405 --> 00:15:03,705
[23.05.16, Samgyetang place,
Min Uk and Hui Won]

271
00:15:03,705 --> 00:15:05,572
[25.02.20, Jang Hui Won
and Cha Min Uk came and left]

272
00:15:05,572 --> 00:15:07,605
[25.07.20, Jang Hui Won
and Cha Min Uk came and left again]

273
00:15:09,972 --> 00:15:11,705
Oh, that startled me...

274
00:15:15,672 --> 00:15:18,405
What's with the graffiti? Did someone
write something bad about you?

275
00:15:18,405 --> 00:15:19,905
Wait... hold on.

276
00:15:19,905 --> 00:15:22,172
I need your approval!

277
00:15:23,138 --> 00:15:26,981
[You finished the whole bowl.
You won't feel sick anymore. Sleep well.]

278
00:15:30,341 --> 00:15:32,905
You were irritated just a moment ago,
and now you're smiling like an idiot.

279
00:15:32,905 --> 00:15:35,005
What did you see? Let me in on the joke.

280
00:15:35,005 --> 00:15:37,405
Just focus on driving.

281
00:15:37,405 --> 00:15:39,938
Both our lives are in your hands.

282
00:15:39,938 --> 00:15:42,905
Since you know that, maybe treat me better?

283
00:15:42,905 --> 00:15:44,972
Talk to me when I'm bored, at least.

284
00:15:44,972 --> 00:15:47,238
Oh right, didn't you say I had some
documents to approve yesterday?

285
00:15:47,238 --> 00:15:49,605
- Where are they?
- You didn't even look when I showed you.

286
00:15:49,605 --> 00:15:54,005
Dear Du Jun doesn't listen to a word I say.

287
00:15:55,838 --> 00:15:57,989
Let me see.

288
00:16:00,105 --> 00:16:01,605
What is this?

289
00:16:01,605 --> 00:16:03,013
[He ate the samgyetang alone]
Why did you doodle

290
00:16:03,013 --> 00:16:04,505
[Am I invisible?]
all over it like this?

291
00:16:04,505 --> 00:16:05,838
And with permanent ink too!

292
00:16:05,838 --> 00:16:06,838
[Jang Hui Won and Cha Min Uk came and left]

293
00:16:06,838 --> 00:16:09,105
Why? Is there a problem?

294
00:16:10,405 --> 00:16:11,538
Well, that...

295
00:16:11,538 --> 00:16:14,038
I forgot to remove that one.

296
00:16:14,038 --> 00:16:16,438
Does forgetting make it all go away?

297
00:16:16,438 --> 00:16:18,505
Then how come you never forget
to use your turn signals when driving?

298
00:16:18,505 --> 00:16:19,805
Forget to eat too.

299
00:16:19,805 --> 00:16:21,305
Forget to come to work.

300
00:16:21,305 --> 00:16:23,005
No, I have to come to work.

301
00:16:23,005 --> 00:16:24,205
Sorry.

302
00:16:24,205 --> 00:16:26,005
Wait, are these scribbles really

303
00:16:26,005 --> 00:16:27,472
worth getting that mad at me?

304
00:16:27,472 --> 00:16:29,838
Of course. I'm very stressed right now.

305
00:16:29,838 --> 00:16:31,705
Focus on driving.

306
00:16:35,505 --> 00:16:37,105
Ah, hurry up!

307
00:16:37,105 --> 00:16:39,372
It's a red light!

308
00:16:40,072 --> 00:16:41,829
- Ugh, seriously.
- Jeez.

309
00:16:41,829 --> 00:16:44,101
[Beer recipe]

310
00:16:46,605 --> 00:16:48,838
Since I can't taste alcohol,

311
00:16:48,838 --> 00:16:51,538
I've got no recipes I can use.

312
00:16:55,372 --> 00:17:00,038
Non-alcoholic beer clearly
has flavor limitations.

313
00:17:07,685 --> 00:17:09,477
[Min Uk]

314
00:17:10,638 --> 00:17:12,372
Oh, Min Uk.

315
00:17:13,305 --> 00:17:15,038
Tomorrow?

316
00:17:16,901 --> 00:17:18,638
Why did you come?

317
00:17:18,638 --> 00:17:19,905
You're only making things take longer.

318
00:17:19,905 --> 00:17:20,972
It's just

319
00:17:20,972 --> 00:17:24,038
I wanted to drive out and chat on the way.

320
00:17:24,038 --> 00:17:28,038
And public transportation's starting
to get hard for you too, right?

321
00:17:31,738 --> 00:17:33,605
Then I'll join you.

322
00:17:33,605 --> 00:17:35,305
Anytime.

323
00:17:50,438 --> 00:17:53,072
Hui Won, are you busy this week?

324
00:17:53,072 --> 00:17:54,072
I have something to tell you.

325
00:17:54,072 --> 00:17:56,272
Something to tell me? Can't you say it now?

326
00:17:56,272 --> 00:18:01,005
Ah, well, it's kind of important.

327
00:18:01,005 --> 00:18:02,238
Yeah?

328
00:18:02,238 --> 00:18:04,805
If you're asking, I'll make time
even if I don't have any.

329
00:18:04,805 --> 00:18:06,538
Wait a second.

330
00:18:09,238 --> 00:18:12,272
[Prenatal Screening]

331
00:18:15,472 --> 00:18:18,372
Why? Are you really busy this week?

332
00:18:18,372 --> 00:18:20,005
Not exactly,

333
00:18:20,005 --> 00:18:23,372
but I have my prenatal screening
and suddenly I'm feeling a bit nervous.

334
00:18:23,372 --> 00:18:26,885
What if the results aren't good?

335
00:18:27,838 --> 00:18:30,538
It'll be fine. Don't worry too much.

336
00:18:30,538 --> 00:18:34,705
Yeah. Thankfully this time,
the President said he'd go with me.

337
00:18:34,705 --> 00:18:35,705
The President?

338
00:18:35,705 --> 00:18:38,372
Yeah, I could go alone,

339
00:18:38,372 --> 00:18:42,505
but since it's an important test,
I feel a little scared.

340
00:18:44,272 --> 00:18:47,705
Oh, I see.

341
00:18:47,705 --> 00:18:48,938
That's a relief.

342
00:18:48,938 --> 00:18:50,672
Yeah.

343
00:19:05,672 --> 00:19:07,238
Level B2.

344
00:19:07,238 --> 00:19:09,638
Doors opening.

345
00:19:09,638 --> 00:19:11,638
Going up.

346
00:19:25,038 --> 00:19:27,238
Doors closing.

347
00:19:35,305 --> 00:19:37,272
Did you two come to work together?

348
00:19:37,272 --> 00:19:40,838
Ah, Min Uk gave me a ride.

349
00:19:41,572 --> 00:19:43,538
- On purpose?
- Intentionally.

350
00:19:43,538 --> 00:19:45,305
Let's just say that.

351
00:19:55,305 --> 00:19:56,572
- Hui Won?
- Yeah?

352
00:19:56,572 --> 00:19:59,872
I heard the owner of that Three O'Clock Pocha
is back after a successful surgery.

353
00:19:59,872 --> 00:20:01,238
Really? Is she doing okay?

354
00:20:01,238 --> 00:20:02,705
Yeah, seems like it.

355
00:20:02,705 --> 00:20:05,772
Last time I walked by the front
and the door was open, so I said hello.

356
00:20:05,772 --> 00:20:07,872
She said we should come by together sometime.

357
00:20:07,872 --> 00:20:10,872
Alright, let's go together and say hello.

358
00:20:10,872 --> 00:20:12,572
Okay.

359
00:20:13,338 --> 00:20:15,738
So it's finally this week.
The day we go to the OB-GYN.

360
00:20:15,738 --> 00:20:18,338
Oh, yes.

361
00:20:18,338 --> 00:20:21,138
Come straight down after work then.
I'll have the car waiting.

362
00:20:21,138 --> 00:20:24,138
It's the day we see our Yeol Mu,
so we can't be late.

363
00:20:24,138 --> 00:20:25,838
'Our'?

364
00:20:27,738 --> 00:20:29,472
Yeah.

365
00:20:38,838 --> 00:20:41,305
- Ah, it's my floor.
- Doors opening.

366
00:20:41,305 --> 00:20:43,805
- Min Uk, bye.
- Okay.

367
00:20:43,805 --> 00:20:45,505
Alright, take care.

368
00:20:45,505 --> 00:20:47,872
Doors closing.

369
00:20:52,005 --> 00:20:54,772
People might get the wrong idea
with you picking her up in the morning.

370
00:20:54,772 --> 00:20:59,405
And you, sir, aren't officially
dating her either, are you?

371
00:21:00,605 --> 00:21:02,005
Do you like Jang Hui Won?

372
00:21:02,005 --> 00:21:03,972
Is that not allowed?

373
00:21:03,972 --> 00:21:05,105
Don't joke around.

374
00:21:05,105 --> 00:21:07,338
I plan to confess to her seriously soon.

375
00:21:07,338 --> 00:21:10,305
Aren't you mistaking friendship for love?

376
00:21:10,305 --> 00:21:15,205
Aren't you the one mistaking
a sense of responsibility for love?

377
00:21:18,505 --> 00:21:21,338
Are you trying to pick a fight right now?

378
00:21:22,472 --> 00:21:23,772
Let's do it.

379
00:21:23,772 --> 00:21:27,672
No ranks, just a fair fight.

380
00:21:30,305 --> 00:21:32,072
[Round 1]

381
00:21:32,072 --> 00:21:34,105
Manager Jang, are you tired?
Can I get you some coffee?

382
00:21:34,105 --> 00:21:35,572
Ah, no thanks.

383
00:21:35,572 --> 00:21:39,205
Slept late last night. Feeling a bit groggy.

384
00:21:39,205 --> 00:21:41,538
A massage would be
perfect on a day like this.

385
00:21:41,538 --> 00:21:43,738
Ugh, I wish someone would just
give me a rubdown.

386
00:21:43,738 --> 00:21:45,905
Tell me about it.

387
00:21:45,905 --> 00:21:47,005
What about you, Tak Soo?

388
00:21:47,005 --> 00:21:49,738
Actually, I have a Level 2
massage certification.

389
00:21:49,738 --> 00:21:51,372
I could give you one later.

390
00:21:51,372 --> 00:21:53,105
- Here.
- What's this?

391
00:21:53,105 --> 00:21:57,538
This is for massaging the neck
and shoulders. It's pretty refreshing.

392
00:21:57,538 --> 00:21:59,405
All of a sudden?

393
00:21:59,405 --> 00:22:00,872
Manager Jang!

394
00:22:00,872 --> 00:22:02,172
- Have you seen it?
- What?

395
00:22:02,172 --> 00:22:04,605
The President just had recliner sofas
delivered to every break room.

396
00:22:04,605 --> 00:22:05,872
Everyone's checking them out right now.

397
00:22:05,872 --> 00:22:07,038
Recliner sofas?

398
00:22:07,038 --> 00:22:09,505
Come on, go take a look.

399
00:22:11,338 --> 00:22:13,038
Let's go.

400
00:22:16,205 --> 00:22:19,205
The President has gifted these,

401
00:22:19,205 --> 00:22:23,172
one for each team, for our hardworking staff.

402
00:22:26,372 --> 00:22:27,772
They're heavily advertised.

403
00:22:27,772 --> 00:22:29,638
As expected of our president.

404
00:22:29,638 --> 00:22:31,525
[Round 2]

405
00:22:36,805 --> 00:22:40,205
Lemon tea, right?
Extra cold, packed with ice?

406
00:22:40,205 --> 00:22:43,772
Lemon tea is for when you're stressed.

407
00:22:44,505 --> 00:22:45,938
Hui Won,

408
00:22:45,938 --> 00:22:48,421
your stomach's been upset lately,
so stick to warm tea.

409
00:22:48,421 --> 00:22:50,972
Here, it's Rooibos.

410
00:22:52,372 --> 00:22:55,372
These are vitamin D and iron supplements,
essential for pregnant women.

411
00:22:55,372 --> 00:22:58,038
Take two pills every morning and evening.

412
00:22:58,038 --> 00:22:59,038
Here, and this

413
00:22:59,038 --> 00:23:01,438
is the macaron you love from the bakery
next to the bank at the intersection.

414
00:23:01,438 --> 00:23:03,638
Eat one whenever you crave sugar, okay?

415
00:23:03,638 --> 00:23:06,705
Isn't it basic knowledge that pregnant women
should avoid sweets?

416
00:23:06,705 --> 00:23:10,072
Don't you know that the stress
of not eating what you crave

417
00:23:10,072 --> 00:23:11,272
is even worse?

418
00:23:11,272 --> 00:23:14,672
When the time comes for those cravings,
I'll naturally buy them for her.

419
00:23:14,672 --> 00:23:18,172
Do you think I can't afford to buy them
because I'm broke or something? Huh?

420
00:23:18,172 --> 00:23:21,072
You keep buying her things.

421
00:23:21,072 --> 00:23:23,305
- Why are you worrying about my child?
- What's going on with those two?

422
00:23:23,305 --> 00:23:24,905
No! How is it your child already?

423
00:23:24,905 --> 00:23:26,772
Isn't it too early to claim paternity?

424
00:23:26,772 --> 00:23:29,505
The baby she's carrying is my child,
so it's my child.

425
00:23:29,505 --> 00:23:32,472
Hey! What if someone hears you?
Be careful what you say.

426
00:23:32,472 --> 00:23:35,038
You keep forgetting I'm your boss.

427
00:23:35,038 --> 00:23:38,138
What exactly are you up to?

428
00:23:41,637 --> 00:23:44,705
Oh, how's the morning sickness lately?

429
00:23:44,705 --> 00:23:48,172
It was bad at first,
but I'm doing better now.

430
00:23:48,172 --> 00:23:51,338
I heard pregnant women
crave sweet and sour things.

431
00:23:51,338 --> 00:23:52,905
Is that true for you too, Manager?

432
00:23:52,905 --> 00:23:56,172
Actually, I've been craving
cold raw fish soup lately.

433
00:23:56,172 --> 00:23:57,872
What's wrong?

434
00:24:02,105 --> 00:24:04,338
- Are they here?
- Who?

435
00:24:05,372 --> 00:24:06,838
No, it's nothing.

436
00:24:06,838 --> 00:24:11,072
There's this place in Pohang
called White Lighthouse.

437
00:24:11,072 --> 00:24:15,405
Their cold raw fish soup is
so refreshing and tangy. It's so good.

438
00:24:15,405 --> 00:24:19,438
Ah, just thinking about it
makes my mouth water.

439
00:24:19,438 --> 00:24:21,838
Wow, please take me there sometime.

440
00:24:21,838 --> 00:24:23,538
- Really?
- Yes.

441
00:24:26,405 --> 00:24:27,938
Cold raw fish soup.

442
00:24:27,938 --> 00:24:30,138
Cold raw fish soup.

443
00:24:30,138 --> 00:24:31,905
Okay.

444
00:24:38,138 --> 00:24:40,965
[Round 3]

445
00:24:45,105 --> 00:24:47,138
[Maksuni Raw Fish Restaurant]
Here.

446
00:24:48,872 --> 00:24:52,205
Yes, can you get it to go right away?

447
00:24:52,205 --> 00:24:53,205
Oh, of course.

448
00:24:53,205 --> 00:24:56,138
In Seoul, no one beats you
when it comes to fresh ingredients.

449
00:24:56,138 --> 00:24:59,405
Yes, thank you.

450
00:25:05,938 --> 00:25:08,472
Secretary Go! Secretary Go!

451
00:25:08,472 --> 00:25:09,893
What? What?

452
00:25:09,893 --> 00:25:11,138
- Is it the only option?
- What?

453
00:25:11,138 --> 00:25:12,438
If we keep this up, we'll lose.

454
00:25:12,438 --> 00:25:15,138
There's no place in Seoul that manages
ingredients as well as that.

455
00:25:15,138 --> 00:25:17,893
I think we're too late.

456
00:25:17,893 --> 00:25:19,429
Darn it!

457
00:25:24,072 --> 00:25:25,772
Then we...

458
00:25:31,505 --> 00:25:32,505
We go to Pohang.

459
00:25:32,505 --> 00:25:33,505
Pohang?

460
00:25:33,505 --> 00:25:34,805
The Pohang I'm thinking of?

461
00:25:34,805 --> 00:25:36,538
What are you talking about?

462
00:25:40,197 --> 00:25:41,338
Whoa.

463
00:25:41,338 --> 00:25:42,638
A helicopter?

464
00:25:42,638 --> 00:25:46,538
Who goes to Pohang just
to buy cold raw fish soup!

465
00:25:47,238 --> 00:25:49,038
The hottest three-star place in Yongsan.

466
00:25:49,038 --> 00:25:52,005
Their ingredient storage
management is top of the industry.

467
00:25:52,005 --> 00:25:55,738
These are flounder and mullet caught directly
at White Lighthouse in Pohang just now.

468
00:25:55,738 --> 00:25:58,238
Wow, did you see that
just now? I think it moved.

469
00:25:58,238 --> 00:26:01,005
How can it be this fresh?

470
00:26:01,005 --> 00:26:03,072
What are you doing here?

471
00:26:03,072 --> 00:26:05,538
Ugh, the smell of food.

472
00:26:05,538 --> 00:26:07,938
That helicopter or freezer truck,
it's all the same.

473
00:26:07,938 --> 00:26:10,738
How is a 5-hour highway drive
the same as a 1-hour helicopter ride?

474
00:26:10,738 --> 00:26:14,872
Anyway, the best catches of the day
all end up at Noryangjin.

475
00:26:14,872 --> 00:26:17,172
Is that it? Oh, that's the end?

476
00:26:17,172 --> 00:26:18,738
No, there's still a long way to go.

477
00:26:18,738 --> 00:26:21,172
Then you can taste it yourself
and choose, Manager Jang.

478
00:26:21,172 --> 00:26:22,338
Good, Hui Won.

479
00:26:22,338 --> 00:26:23,372
Is it the President, or me?

480
00:26:23,372 --> 00:26:24,872
Me, or him?

481
00:26:24,872 --> 00:26:27,072
- Look.
- Look.

482
00:26:27,072 --> 00:26:28,338
- Is it the President, or me?
- Taste it.

483
00:26:28,338 --> 00:26:30,572
- Just take one bite.
- Smell it, Hui Won.

484
00:26:30,572 --> 00:26:32,772
Stop! Stop!

485
00:26:32,772 --> 00:26:36,538
If you don't want to get sliced
like raw fish, get out right now.

486
00:26:36,538 --> 00:26:37,772
Get out.

487
00:26:37,772 --> 00:26:39,505
Get out!

488
00:26:40,505 --> 00:26:41,705
Get out!

489
00:26:41,705 --> 00:26:43,438
Get out quickly!

490
00:26:44,238 --> 00:26:45,938
Go!

491
00:26:51,538 --> 00:26:53,538
Beautiful thoughts,

492
00:26:53,538 --> 00:26:55,538
good thoughts.

493
00:26:59,938 --> 00:27:01,838
It's bland broth, totally bland.

494
00:27:01,838 --> 00:27:03,072
Isn't this just soup with chili paste?

495
00:27:03,072 --> 00:27:06,005
- Is this from White Lighthouse now...
- Abandoned souls,

496
00:27:06,005 --> 00:27:08,005
follow me.

497
00:27:09,972 --> 00:27:11,872
What did he say?

498
00:27:14,572 --> 00:27:17,038
Didn't you voluntarily come in on weekends,
saying you were motivated?

499
00:27:17,038 --> 00:27:18,568
From what I see, Manager Nah,

500
00:27:18,568 --> 00:27:21,072
your determination
lasts not three days, but one.

501
00:27:21,072 --> 00:27:22,885
If he keeps that up, he'll get
scolded by the Team Leader.

502
00:27:22,885 --> 00:27:24,105
Oh.

503
00:27:24,105 --> 00:27:25,672
Oh, that startled me.

504
00:27:25,672 --> 00:27:28,805
The chair was so comfortable,
so I closed my eyes without realizing it.

505
00:27:28,805 --> 00:27:30,805
Our company benefits
have gotten way too good lately.

506
00:27:30,805 --> 00:27:32,138
I wonder if there'll be
anything left at this rate?

507
00:27:32,138 --> 00:27:35,472
But it looks like Manager Nah
enjoys those benefits the most.

508
00:27:35,472 --> 00:27:38,538
That's right. At the last beef dinner,
you ate like there was no tomorrow.

509
00:27:38,538 --> 00:27:39,872
And I saw you even had
two bowls of jjamppong.

510
00:27:39,872 --> 00:27:43,305
You clock in at the lounge every day
just to use the recliner sofa.

511
00:27:43,305 --> 00:27:45,472
Assistant Manager Choi,
isn't that sofa meant to be used?

512
00:27:45,472 --> 00:27:48,405
Anyway, since the President came,
the benefits are on another level.

513
00:27:48,405 --> 00:27:50,672
As they say, a fish rots from the head down.

514
00:27:50,672 --> 00:27:52,229
Our team is first-grade water!

515
00:27:52,229 --> 00:27:53,305
First-grade!

516
00:27:53,305 --> 00:27:55,038
Are you sure?

517
00:27:56,105 --> 00:27:57,105
That it's first-grade?

518
00:27:57,105 --> 00:27:59,038
Team Leader, where did you pop up from?

519
00:27:59,038 --> 00:28:00,372
Did you set an alarm or something?

520
00:28:00,372 --> 00:28:03,072
If the manager's always gossiping,
what do you expect from the rest?

521
00:28:03,072 --> 00:28:04,405
Haven't you heard? 'The pupil
surpasses the master.'

522
00:28:04,405 --> 00:28:06,338
Our team members are so capable.

523
00:28:06,338 --> 00:28:08,705
You sure talk a good game.
Alright, let's get back to work.

524
00:28:08,705 --> 00:28:11,338
Unless you want to work weekends again.

525
00:28:11,338 --> 00:28:12,338
Yes.

526
00:28:12,338 --> 00:28:13,605
By the way, Team Leader,

527
00:28:13,605 --> 00:28:15,638
where have you been going?

528
00:28:15,638 --> 00:28:17,905
You've been away a lot. Don't tell me...

529
00:28:17,905 --> 00:28:21,505
I think I saw you in the lounge earlier, too.

530
00:28:21,505 --> 00:28:22,505
I also passed by the lounge...

531
00:28:22,505 --> 00:28:26,705
Alright, let's get back
to work diligently. Fighting!

532
00:28:27,493 --> 00:28:29,172
Jeez.

533
00:28:29,172 --> 00:28:30,972
- Saw her in the lounge?
- You did?

534
00:28:30,972 --> 00:28:33,238
- I did.
- In the lounge?

535
00:28:34,672 --> 00:28:35,705
[Round 4]

536
00:28:35,705 --> 00:28:38,638
Alright.

537
00:28:38,638 --> 00:28:42,505
Stop growling at each other,
drink up and make up.

538
00:28:42,505 --> 00:28:44,872
Who's growling?

539
00:28:44,872 --> 00:28:46,469
Come on.

540
00:28:47,805 --> 00:28:50,038
Huh? Uh, hold on.

541
00:28:53,338 --> 00:28:55,272
It's not about drinking like this.

542
00:28:55,272 --> 00:28:58,472
It's about cheers and making up.

543
00:28:58,472 --> 00:29:00,605
Cheers!

544
00:29:00,605 --> 00:29:02,072
I'm drinking this time too.

545
00:29:02,072 --> 00:29:04,705
No, no.

546
00:29:12,772 --> 00:29:15,705
Ugh, this doubles my stress. Doubles it.

547
00:29:15,705 --> 00:29:18,805
You know, when I get stressed,
my stomach really acts up.

548
00:29:19,872 --> 00:29:22,272
Oh no, here it is right now.

549
00:29:22,272 --> 00:29:24,205
Ugh, I need the restroom.

550
00:29:24,205 --> 00:29:27,938
While I'm in the restroom,
you two make up on your own.

551
00:29:27,938 --> 00:29:29,305
After all that cheering. Cheers!

552
00:29:29,305 --> 00:29:31,005
Sit down.

553
00:29:34,638 --> 00:29:37,538
Oh no, I'm not gonna make it.

554
00:29:48,338 --> 00:29:50,338
Did you confess?

555
00:29:52,138 --> 00:29:54,805
Do I have to say it?

556
00:29:54,805 --> 00:29:56,672
You haven't done it yet, huh?

557
00:29:59,438 --> 00:30:02,172
I haven't done it. Yet.

558
00:30:02,172 --> 00:30:03,672
You mean you couldn't do it.

559
00:30:03,672 --> 00:30:06,638
Why? Because you're dealing with me.

560
00:30:07,605 --> 00:30:11,672
How can one night compete with fifteen years?

561
00:30:14,072 --> 00:30:18,038
Do you know what Hui Won likes to eat?

562
00:30:18,738 --> 00:30:22,605
Her hobbies or habits?
Neighborhoods she frequents? Regular shops?

563
00:30:24,038 --> 00:30:25,372
Ah, what?

564
00:30:25,372 --> 00:30:28,372
You don't even properly know
about Hui Won, and then,

565
00:30:28,372 --> 00:30:29,701
you've even confessed?

566
00:30:29,701 --> 00:30:30,705
What?

567
00:30:30,705 --> 00:30:33,972
You seem to occasionally
forget that I'm the company president.

568
00:30:33,972 --> 00:30:35,205
Wow, petty.

569
00:30:35,205 --> 00:30:39,105
Didn't we agree to drop
the ranks and play fair?

570
00:30:39,105 --> 00:30:41,338
Another bottle of soju here, please.

571
00:30:41,338 --> 00:30:43,472
Just bring three bottles.

572
00:30:43,472 --> 00:30:45,638
Looks like we'll finish them quickly.

573
00:31:11,072 --> 00:31:13,738
Why are they both doing this to me?

574
00:31:13,738 --> 00:31:16,472
Why is the President making
it so obvious at work?

575
00:31:16,472 --> 00:31:19,005
What if someone sees?

576
00:31:19,005 --> 00:31:20,738
And what's with him all of a sudden?

577
00:31:20,738 --> 00:31:23,872
What if he gets fired from the company
for competing with the President?

578
00:31:24,938 --> 00:31:27,805
Jeez, why is everyone like this?

579
00:31:27,805 --> 00:31:30,638
I'm tired. Seriously.

580
00:31:30,638 --> 00:31:33,541
Seems like alcohol doesn't sit well
with you, Assistant Manager Cha.

581
00:31:33,541 --> 00:31:35,005
Go on.

582
00:31:35,005 --> 00:31:36,805
- You are drunk.
- Drink.

583
00:31:36,805 --> 00:31:38,472
How much did you drink in such a short time?

584
00:31:38,472 --> 00:31:41,005
President, do you know
how petty the President is?

585
00:31:41,005 --> 00:31:43,905
- I'm the President?
- He gave me this much paperwork

586
00:31:43,905 --> 00:31:46,472
and told me to sort it out within a week.

587
00:31:46,472 --> 00:31:47,538
No.

588
00:31:47,538 --> 00:31:50,372
You are saying things
they won't even remember.

589
00:31:50,372 --> 00:31:51,538
Let's go home. Let's go home.

590
00:31:51,538 --> 00:31:53,705
Mister, I didn't call a designated driver.
Leave. Hurry.

591
00:31:53,705 --> 00:31:55,138
What are you talking about?

592
00:31:55,138 --> 00:31:56,738
- Let's go home.
- No.

593
00:31:56,738 --> 00:31:59,005
Excuse me!

594
00:31:59,005 --> 00:32:01,305
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

595
00:32:01,305 --> 00:32:04,172
Assistant Manager Cha,
you call a designated driver.

596
00:32:04,172 --> 00:32:06,272
I don't have a car.

597
00:32:09,005 --> 00:32:10,105
What, you're sleeping now?

598
00:32:10,105 --> 00:32:13,172
Let's go home. Let's go home. Huh?

599
00:32:13,172 --> 00:32:14,872
Ow, hot.

600
00:32:14,872 --> 00:32:16,838
Home...

601
00:32:16,838 --> 00:32:18,472
Let's go home.

602
00:32:18,472 --> 00:32:22,372
[Game Over]
Who am I talking to?

603
00:32:23,525 --> 00:32:25,189
Wait...

604
00:32:26,872 --> 00:32:28,638
President.

605
00:32:29,438 --> 00:32:30,572
What is all this?

606
00:32:30,572 --> 00:32:34,338
I didn't know what you'd like,
so I bought everything.

607
00:32:34,338 --> 00:32:37,338
Chicken, pizza, tteokbokki, sushi...

608
00:32:37,338 --> 00:32:40,905
And this... desserts and salad too.

609
00:32:40,905 --> 00:32:41,972
All of this?

610
00:32:41,972 --> 00:32:45,772
But what exactly is your favorite food?

611
00:32:45,772 --> 00:32:47,005
- What?
- Your hobbies?

612
00:32:47,005 --> 00:32:51,205
I mean, not those random places,
just neighborhoods you often go to,

613
00:32:51,205 --> 00:32:54,272
or regular shops you visit.

614
00:32:54,272 --> 00:32:58,438
Did you come here in the middle
of the night to ask that?

615
00:32:58,438 --> 00:33:00,872
Assistant Manager Cha knows everything.

616
00:33:00,872 --> 00:33:02,872
He knows you can't handle spice

617
00:33:02,872 --> 00:33:06,005
so you eat malatang at level 0.5.

618
00:33:06,005 --> 00:33:09,672
He knows you choose spicy cold noodles
over plain cold noodles after meat.

619
00:33:09,672 --> 00:33:12,438
He knows everything. Only I don't know.

620
00:33:12,438 --> 00:33:16,038
Are you still not done
with that childish ego fight?

621
00:33:16,038 --> 00:33:17,705
Please stop.

622
00:33:17,705 --> 00:33:20,038
What if someone starts suspecting something?

623
00:33:20,038 --> 00:33:23,505
Ms. Jang Hui Won,
is that really so important?

624
00:33:23,505 --> 00:33:24,705
Of course it is.

625
00:33:24,705 --> 00:33:28,405
If our relationship is exposed,
I'm the one who'll be judged.

626
00:33:28,405 --> 00:33:31,772
No, no, no.

627
00:33:31,772 --> 00:33:35,138
What you're worried about won't happen.

628
00:33:35,138 --> 00:33:37,538
I'll block it all for you.

629
00:33:49,861 --> 00:33:51,461
You...

630
00:33:56,205 --> 00:33:58,072
Ugh, jeez.

631
00:33:58,072 --> 00:34:01,205
I told them to make up,
but what time is it now, seriously?

632
00:34:01,205 --> 00:34:03,638
Ugh, I'm stressed. She's not
off work already, is she?

633
00:34:03,638 --> 00:34:04,805
Hold on.

634
00:34:04,805 --> 00:34:05,861
Oh.

635
00:34:05,861 --> 00:34:07,461
Oh, Secretary Go.

636
00:34:07,461 --> 00:34:13,038
I didn't just pick it up.
I bought it for you.

637
00:34:13,038 --> 00:34:16,338
Thank you. It's warm.

638
00:34:16,338 --> 00:34:19,172
Secretary Go, you haven't left work yet?

639
00:34:19,172 --> 00:34:23,305
I suppose this is the fate
of a secretary serving the President.

640
00:34:25,272 --> 00:34:26,772
What about you, Team Leader Bang?

641
00:34:26,772 --> 00:34:29,472
Are you working this late?

642
00:34:29,472 --> 00:34:33,605
I suppose this is the fate
of a team leader guiding a team.

643
00:34:33,605 --> 00:34:36,438
People call me ruthless, but I enjoy working.

644
00:34:36,438 --> 00:34:38,605
Because mistakes aren't tolerated.

645
00:34:38,605 --> 00:34:40,105
That's admirable.

646
00:34:40,105 --> 00:34:43,272
Not ruthless, just impressive.

647
00:34:43,272 --> 00:34:46,972
This is the way I see you, Team Leader.

648
00:35:37,305 --> 00:35:39,072
Take it.

649
00:35:39,072 --> 00:35:40,901
That seems like an important call.

650
00:35:40,901 --> 00:35:43,905
Completely clueless.

651
00:35:43,905 --> 00:35:45,272
Then excuse me.

652
00:35:45,272 --> 00:35:47,005
Okay.

653
00:35:48,538 --> 00:35:50,538
Yes.

654
00:35:50,538 --> 00:35:52,672
What? The President?

655
00:35:52,672 --> 00:35:55,405
Why there? I just took him home.

656
00:36:09,872 --> 00:36:13,172
Jeez, sober up before you leave.

657
00:36:13,172 --> 00:36:15,305
You're in no condition to even take a taxi.

658
00:36:15,305 --> 00:36:18,438
Why did you drink so much?
What if you get sick again?

659
00:36:18,438 --> 00:36:21,372
I didn't want to lose.

660
00:36:21,372 --> 00:36:23,772
What's so important about winning or losing?

661
00:36:23,772 --> 00:36:24,805
It matters.

662
00:36:24,805 --> 00:36:29,305
In the men's world, that's crucial.

663
00:36:29,305 --> 00:36:33,638
Anyway, I won't disturb you. Get some rest.

664
00:36:33,638 --> 00:36:36,738
I can't sleep.

665
00:36:36,738 --> 00:36:39,238
Can I just stay

666
00:36:39,238 --> 00:36:41,905
five more minutes?

667
00:36:51,072 --> 00:36:52,438
Alright.

668
00:36:52,438 --> 00:36:56,205
But only five minutes.

669
00:37:08,838 --> 00:37:13,038
Do you remember when we met in Itaewon?

670
00:37:13,038 --> 00:37:15,105
I remember.

671
00:37:15,105 --> 00:37:16,372
How could I forget?

672
00:37:16,372 --> 00:37:18,072
For me, that day

673
00:37:18,072 --> 00:37:21,038
was really wonderful.

674
00:37:21,038 --> 00:37:23,372
Laughing and chatting together,

675
00:37:23,372 --> 00:37:26,305
drinking and playing games,

676
00:37:27,638 --> 00:37:29,905
even running away together.

677
00:37:30,738 --> 00:37:33,138
All of it felt even better

678
00:37:33,138 --> 00:37:36,138
because I was with you, Ms. Jang Hui Won.

679
00:37:36,138 --> 00:37:38,172
Whether I'm a boss,

680
00:37:38,172 --> 00:37:41,605
an employee, or some heir,

681
00:37:41,605 --> 00:37:43,621
just

682
00:37:43,621 --> 00:37:46,272
man to man...

683
00:37:47,705 --> 00:37:51,372
No, man to woman...

684
00:37:55,938 --> 00:37:59,205
I know what you're struggling with.

685
00:37:59,205 --> 00:38:02,505
All I can say right now is this.

686
00:38:03,138 --> 00:38:09,072
I won't let you face any situation alone.

687
00:38:09,772 --> 00:38:13,605
And I will absolutely never

688
00:38:15,405 --> 00:38:18,338
let go of your hand again.

689
00:39:27,138 --> 00:39:28,438
When did you get here?

690
00:39:28,438 --> 00:39:29,838
Drink this, first.

691
00:39:29,838 --> 00:39:31,138
It's exactly what you need right now.

692
00:39:31,138 --> 00:39:34,138
Ugh, my head feels like it's splitting.

693
00:39:34,138 --> 00:39:35,938
What happened last night?

694
00:39:35,938 --> 00:39:38,438
Don't you remember? At all?

695
00:39:40,338 --> 00:39:42,305
I don't remember anything.

696
00:39:43,338 --> 00:39:44,972
Why? Did something happen?

697
00:39:44,972 --> 00:39:46,472
Pray to the heavens.

698
00:39:46,472 --> 00:39:48,172
That's better for your mental health.

699
00:39:48,172 --> 00:39:49,238
What nonsense are you talking about?

700
00:39:49,238 --> 00:39:51,938
I seriously thought I was dreaming.

701
00:39:51,938 --> 00:39:53,972
I definitely took you home last night.

702
00:39:53,972 --> 00:39:56,172
But when I came to,

703
00:39:56,172 --> 00:39:58,305
I was taking you home again.

704
00:39:58,305 --> 00:40:00,705
What kind of nonsense is this?

705
00:40:00,705 --> 00:40:03,805
What nonsense? Seems like
you're the drunk one.

706
00:40:06,005 --> 00:40:08,101
- Ah, my throat hurts too.
- I'm sure it does.

707
00:40:08,101 --> 00:40:09,472
[Jang Hui Won]

708
00:40:09,472 --> 00:40:11,205
You got home safely last night, right?

709
00:40:11,205 --> 00:40:13,538
Is your hangover any better?

710
00:40:13,538 --> 00:40:15,838
What? How did she know all this?

711
00:40:15,838 --> 00:40:17,005
What is all this?

712
00:40:17,005 --> 00:40:18,872
I didn't know what you'd like.

713
00:40:18,872 --> 00:40:22,672
Chicken, pizza, tteokbokki, even salad.

714
00:40:22,672 --> 00:40:24,005
I can't sleep.

715
00:40:24,005 --> 00:40:26,438
Can I just stay five more minutes?

716
00:40:26,438 --> 00:40:29,005
I'm sorry. He kept trying to call a taxi.

717
00:40:29,005 --> 00:40:30,872
No, this is my duty.

718
00:40:30,872 --> 00:40:32,072
You should head inside.

719
00:40:32,072 --> 00:40:35,638
Who are you? I haven't called a taxi yet.

720
00:40:36,272 --> 00:40:38,505
This is a deluxe taxi,
so fares are quadruple.

721
00:40:38,505 --> 00:40:39,872
Then I won't take it.

722
00:40:39,872 --> 00:40:40,905
I'll take a regular one.

723
00:40:40,905 --> 00:40:42,105
What do you mean?

724
00:40:42,105 --> 00:40:44,138
- Get in quick.
- Who are you?

725
00:40:46,738 --> 00:40:48,738
Take care now.

726
00:40:48,738 --> 00:40:50,772
Okay, then.

727
00:40:50,772 --> 00:40:52,672
Mister.

728
00:40:52,672 --> 00:40:54,572
- Yes.
- Yes, then...

729
00:40:57,669 --> 00:41:00,838
Huh?

730
00:41:00,838 --> 00:41:01,861
No.

731
00:41:01,861 --> 00:41:04,645
- Ugh.
- Ugh.

732
00:41:09,805 --> 00:41:12,472
You remember now?

733
00:41:16,005 --> 00:41:18,438
Gosh, I'm so anxious.

734
00:41:18,438 --> 00:41:20,138
Oh, you startled me.

735
00:41:22,872 --> 00:41:24,229
Tastes good.

736
00:41:24,229 --> 00:41:26,341
Ugh.

737
00:41:28,517 --> 00:41:30,661
Good work.

738
00:41:30,661 --> 00:41:31,772
But I think...

739
00:41:31,772 --> 00:41:35,005
I'm sorry about yesterday, in many ways.

740
00:41:36,405 --> 00:41:38,705
Why didn't you pick up your phone?

741
00:41:42,853 --> 00:41:46,438
You go on ahead.

742
00:41:46,438 --> 00:41:48,172
See you later.

743
00:41:57,253 --> 00:41:58,533
[OB-GYN]

744
00:42:00,133 --> 00:42:01,733
[OB-GYN]
Found it through a director I know.

745
00:42:01,733 --> 00:42:03,805
Call them.

746
00:42:03,805 --> 00:42:06,405
It's a safe and reliable place.

747
00:42:08,105 --> 00:42:10,572
Did you come here to give me this?

748
00:42:10,572 --> 00:42:12,672
If you'd answered my call,
I wouldn't have come.

749
00:42:12,672 --> 00:42:15,305
Aren't you going to get rid of it anyway?

750
00:42:15,305 --> 00:42:17,438
Mom, I'm going to keep the baby.

751
00:42:17,438 --> 00:42:20,038
I told you I'm keeping this baby.

752
00:42:20,038 --> 00:42:21,872
Ugh, jeez.

753
00:42:21,872 --> 00:42:23,505
I thought

754
00:42:23,505 --> 00:42:26,838
you came because of
the texts you sent last time.

755
00:42:26,838 --> 00:42:29,205
Guess I was a fool to hope for that.

756
00:42:31,672 --> 00:42:34,205
What does the baby's father do?

757
00:42:34,205 --> 00:42:35,838
Enough. I don't want to talk about it now.

758
00:42:35,838 --> 00:42:37,638
I'm not even curious.

759
00:42:37,638 --> 00:42:40,838
Hearing about some reckless guy who got
someone else's daughter pregnant won't help.

760
00:42:40,838 --> 00:42:42,872
He's not that kind of person.

761
00:42:42,872 --> 00:42:44,405
Since when can you read people?

762
00:42:44,405 --> 00:42:46,305
What are you going to do now?

763
00:42:46,305 --> 00:42:48,305
Are you thinking about marriage?

764
00:42:49,205 --> 00:42:52,038
Marriage is still...

765
00:42:54,205 --> 00:42:57,172
No, not him, it's me.

766
00:42:57,172 --> 00:42:58,605
I haven't thought that far ahead.

767
00:42:58,605 --> 00:42:59,705
Exactly.

768
00:42:59,705 --> 00:43:03,738
You got yourself into this mess
without planning to get married, didn't you?

769
00:43:03,738 --> 00:43:05,505
Oh, my head.

770
00:43:06,872 --> 00:43:09,005
I raised you wrong.

771
00:43:11,072 --> 00:43:12,105
Mom!

772
00:43:12,105 --> 00:43:13,538
Fine. I won't interfere.

773
00:43:13,538 --> 00:43:14,938
Whether you regret having the baby

774
00:43:14,938 --> 00:43:16,872
or cry over a man,

775
00:43:16,872 --> 00:43:18,805
would you even listen if I stopped you?

776
00:43:18,805 --> 00:43:20,772
It's your life, so you handle it now.

777
00:43:20,772 --> 00:43:22,772
I'm staying out of it.

778
00:43:23,672 --> 00:43:25,372
Mom.

779
00:43:29,805 --> 00:43:32,038
Oh, jeez.

780
00:43:44,805 --> 00:43:46,938
With the recent Taehan Liquor issues,

781
00:43:46,938 --> 00:43:48,905
the board's mood was tense?

782
00:43:48,905 --> 00:43:50,772
Oh, yes.

783
00:43:50,772 --> 00:43:54,538
But it seems it's been
relatively well managed.

784
00:43:54,538 --> 00:43:56,905
The stock price stabilized quickly,

785
00:43:56,905 --> 00:44:00,105
and the board meeting went
smoothly without major disputes.

786
00:44:00,105 --> 00:44:01,105
That's how it should be.

787
00:44:01,105 --> 00:44:04,138
Du Jun isn't exactly irresponsible.

788
00:44:04,772 --> 00:44:06,005
So, the thing is,

789
00:44:06,005 --> 00:44:10,638
I've been feeling stiff
and pretty bored lately.

790
00:44:10,638 --> 00:44:13,605
How about I start getting back to work?

791
00:44:14,405 --> 00:44:15,805
- Back to work?
- Yes.

792
00:44:15,805 --> 00:44:17,372
Why? Is it a bit too early?

793
00:44:17,372 --> 00:44:21,672
No, I'm fine with it.

794
00:44:21,672 --> 00:44:24,805
I'm just concerned about your health.

795
00:44:24,805 --> 00:44:26,605
Your heart condition,

796
00:44:26,605 --> 00:44:29,838
and blood pressure need careful management.

797
00:44:29,838 --> 00:44:31,605
It sounds like you're advising against it.

798
00:44:31,605 --> 00:44:33,572
Huh? That's not it.

799
00:44:33,572 --> 00:44:34,805
- What I meant was...
- Oh dear.

800
00:44:34,805 --> 00:44:35,938
Just joking, joking.

801
00:44:35,938 --> 00:44:40,738
I never knew my little brother cared
so much about my health.

802
00:44:40,738 --> 00:44:42,038
- Yes.
- Let's drink.

803
00:44:42,038 --> 00:44:43,813
Yes.

804
00:44:43,813 --> 00:44:45,221
Let's drink.

805
00:44:49,797 --> 00:44:51,301
Good.

806
00:44:53,272 --> 00:44:54,605
I expected that.

807
00:44:54,605 --> 00:44:58,338
Don't worry. I'll speak with him.

808
00:45:02,672 --> 00:45:04,705
Father-in-law.

809
00:45:04,705 --> 00:45:08,072
If he would just stay put,
no one would get hurt.

810
00:45:08,072 --> 00:45:10,838
He keeps bringing this on himself.

811
00:45:15,973 --> 00:45:17,738
Oh, I'm exhausted.

812
00:45:17,738 --> 00:45:21,438
I shouldn't have suggested it.
I'm the only one suffering.

813
00:45:36,872 --> 00:45:38,172
Did you get home safely yesterday?

814
00:45:38,172 --> 00:45:39,905
Actually, not really.

815
00:45:39,905 --> 00:45:41,672
- What?
- I said not really.

816
00:45:41,672 --> 00:45:44,872
You're not telling me you don't remember
a single thing from yesterday, huh?

817
00:45:44,872 --> 00:45:47,272
What happened yesterday?

818
00:45:47,272 --> 00:45:49,605
Ugh, I knew it.

819
00:45:49,605 --> 00:45:51,072
In all my years,

820
00:45:51,072 --> 00:45:55,172
I've never seen a messy drunk
as bad as you, Assistant Manager Cha.

821
00:45:55,172 --> 00:45:57,005
No, I'm not a messy drunk.

822
00:45:57,005 --> 00:45:59,672
Even at company dinners,
I've handled my alcohol well.

823
00:45:59,672 --> 00:46:01,638
Oh, really?

824
00:46:01,638 --> 00:46:04,105
Then why did you mistake the office for home?

825
00:46:04,105 --> 00:46:05,638
While searching for you,

826
00:46:05,638 --> 00:46:09,105
do you know how many elevator trips I made?

827
00:46:09,105 --> 00:46:10,238
I did that?

828
00:46:10,238 --> 00:46:12,305
You asked how I found your address.

829
00:46:12,305 --> 00:46:14,505
Oh, and said you wanted to be friends.

830
00:46:14,505 --> 00:46:16,538
All while giving me that look.

831
00:46:16,538 --> 00:46:19,338
How could you forget?

832
00:46:19,338 --> 00:46:21,472
Oh, come on.

833
00:46:22,872 --> 00:46:24,538
Weren't you drunk, Secretary Go?

834
00:46:24,538 --> 00:46:25,572
Guess you drank too much.

835
00:46:25,572 --> 00:46:28,038
I didn't even drink.

836
00:46:28,038 --> 00:46:31,038
It was all recorded on the CCTV here.

837
00:46:33,272 --> 00:46:34,738
Secretary Go.

838
00:46:34,738 --> 00:46:38,238
You're joking because you
want to get closer to me, right?

839
00:46:40,205 --> 00:46:41,638
This is me.

840
00:46:41,638 --> 00:46:44,305
See you next time. Have a good day.

841
00:46:45,805 --> 00:46:48,133
Another annoying person.

842
00:46:48,133 --> 00:46:49,765
Jeez.

843
00:46:57,505 --> 00:46:58,872
Father.

844
00:46:58,872 --> 00:47:00,838
Huh?

845
00:47:00,838 --> 00:47:02,805
What brings you here?

846
00:47:05,072 --> 00:47:07,272
You're returning to work?

847
00:47:08,372 --> 00:47:10,105
Yeah.

848
00:47:12,138 --> 00:47:16,238
I wondered why you've been
so fearless lately. Now I see the reason.

849
00:47:16,238 --> 00:47:19,138
You know Han Jun's memorial day
is coming up soon, right?

850
00:47:19,138 --> 00:47:22,172
Give me Taehan Liquor.

851
00:47:23,705 --> 00:47:26,138
It was supposed to be Han Jun's anyway.

852
00:47:30,972 --> 00:47:32,005
What if I say no?

853
00:47:32,005 --> 00:47:36,772
You'll see for yourself why you
have no choice but to say yes.

854
00:47:44,138 --> 00:47:45,572
It's fine. Forget it.

855
00:47:45,572 --> 00:47:48,238
What do I expect from Mom?

856
00:47:48,238 --> 00:47:51,705
Haven't I always lived my own life?

857
00:47:54,438 --> 00:47:56,172
Hui Won.

858
00:47:57,938 --> 00:48:00,105
When did you get here?

859
00:48:00,105 --> 00:48:03,305
Can we talk for a minute?

860
00:48:04,105 --> 00:48:06,605
You had drinks with the President
yesterday, right?

861
00:48:06,605 --> 00:48:08,472
Huh?

862
00:48:09,338 --> 00:48:11,005
- Yeah.
- Is something wrong?

863
00:48:11,005 --> 00:48:13,305
You've been acting strange lately.

864
00:48:13,305 --> 00:48:14,853
- What have I done?
- You keep acting childish

865
00:48:14,853 --> 00:48:16,238
while competing with the President.

866
00:48:16,238 --> 00:48:18,172
Even had a pride contest over drinks.

867
00:48:18,172 --> 00:48:21,272
If you're trying to
save face for me, just stop.

868
00:48:21,272 --> 00:48:25,972
I feel like I'm the only weird one
between you two.

869
00:48:25,972 --> 00:48:28,205
What if I don't want that?

870
00:48:28,205 --> 00:48:31,205
- Huh?
- Do you really not know

871
00:48:31,205 --> 00:48:32,205
why I'm like this?

872
00:48:32,205 --> 00:48:33,805
Hello, Manager Jang.

873
00:48:33,805 --> 00:48:35,972
Hello.

874
00:48:37,925 --> 00:48:40,972
Sorry, what did you just say?

875
00:48:41,938 --> 00:48:43,505
Nothing.

876
00:48:43,505 --> 00:48:45,605
Let's talk another time.

877
00:48:58,538 --> 00:49:00,405
Check-out is at 11 a.m.,

878
00:49:00,405 --> 00:49:03,472
and the elevators are straight
ahead on your left.

879
00:49:03,472 --> 00:49:06,005
Enjoy your stay.

880
00:49:16,872 --> 00:49:17,872
Busy?

881
00:49:17,872 --> 00:49:22,172
He hasn't confessed
to Hui Won already, has he?

882
00:49:22,172 --> 00:49:23,905
Hwang Mi Ran,

883
00:49:23,905 --> 00:49:27,005
why did you end up falling for Cha Min Uk?

884
00:49:29,605 --> 00:49:30,838
[Myeongwoon University Pop-Up Bar]

885
00:49:30,838 --> 00:49:32,072
[7 Years Ago]
Cheers!

886
00:49:32,072 --> 00:49:34,821
[7 Years Ago]

887
00:49:34,821 --> 00:49:36,305
Try this!

888
00:49:36,305 --> 00:49:38,205
I won't get drunk today.

889
00:49:38,205 --> 00:49:39,738
By the way, where's Sang Woo?

890
00:49:39,738 --> 00:49:42,072
No idea. Maybe he's camped out
at the PC bang again?

891
00:49:42,072 --> 00:49:43,638
You said he pulled an all-nighter
there yesterday.

892
00:49:43,638 --> 00:49:47,138
Yeah. If he weren't so handsome,
I'd have dumped him.

893
00:49:47,138 --> 00:49:48,505
Ugh, I'm exhausted.

894
00:49:48,505 --> 00:49:51,638
I invited a friend from another department.
Can we drink together?

895
00:49:51,638 --> 00:49:54,305
Friend? Who? Is he a guy?

896
00:49:54,305 --> 00:49:55,505
He's a friend from middle school.

897
00:49:55,505 --> 00:49:56,705
He went on an exchange program

898
00:49:56,705 --> 00:49:58,872
and is now back in Korea for a short while.

899
00:49:58,872 --> 00:50:01,138
Oh, Jang Hui Won, you have
a guy friend like that?

900
00:50:01,138 --> 00:50:03,472
Hey, invite him! Call him now!

901
00:50:03,472 --> 00:50:05,838
I already did.

902
00:50:06,705 --> 00:50:08,938
Huh? Min Uk?

903
00:50:13,205 --> 00:50:15,238
- It's been a while.
- Yeah.

904
00:50:18,072 --> 00:50:19,072
I told you about her.

905
00:50:19,072 --> 00:50:20,389
This is Mi Ran.

906
00:50:20,389 --> 00:50:22,117
Oh.

907
00:50:23,872 --> 00:50:25,605
Hi.

908
00:50:25,605 --> 00:50:27,338
Hi.

909
00:50:28,072 --> 00:50:29,105
Wanna drink?

910
00:50:29,105 --> 00:50:30,305
What do you like to drink?

911
00:50:30,305 --> 00:50:32,505
We're beer people,
but soju-beer mix is fine too.

912
00:50:32,505 --> 00:50:34,438
No, I like beer too.

913
00:50:34,438 --> 00:50:36,438
- Really?
- Yeah.

914
00:50:37,705 --> 00:50:39,438
Thank you.

915
00:50:39,438 --> 00:50:41,893
[Hangover Remedy]

916
00:50:41,893 --> 00:50:42,905
Oh.

917
00:50:42,905 --> 00:50:44,672
I'll go get more beer.

918
00:50:44,672 --> 00:50:47,672
Stay put. I'll get it.

919
00:50:50,738 --> 00:50:52,538
You'll need more of this, right?

920
00:50:56,372 --> 00:50:57,705
Hey.

921
00:50:57,705 --> 00:50:59,538
What's with him? Why's he so sweet?

922
00:50:59,538 --> 00:51:02,672
The kindness just flows
out of him like breathing.

923
00:51:02,672 --> 00:51:03,972
Min Uk's kind, right?

924
00:51:03,972 --> 00:51:04,972
Considerate, too.

925
00:51:04,972 --> 00:51:06,705
Yeah.

926
00:51:07,405 --> 00:51:10,372
[Pop-up Bar]
I'll take a beer, sir.

927
00:51:10,372 --> 00:51:12,105
What?

928
00:51:13,105 --> 00:51:16,357
[2 Years Ago]

929
00:51:24,272 --> 00:51:26,872
Huh? Cha Min Uk.

930
00:51:27,705 --> 00:51:31,072
Jeez, you are drinking alone again.

931
00:51:31,072 --> 00:51:32,105
Where's Hui Won?

932
00:51:32,105 --> 00:51:33,381
She's working late today.

933
00:51:33,381 --> 00:51:34,821
Oh.

934
00:51:36,005 --> 00:51:38,338
Is there ever a day Jang Hui Won isn't busy?

935
00:51:38,338 --> 00:51:40,205
True.

936
00:51:42,038 --> 00:51:45,238
You're the best, as always.

937
00:51:45,238 --> 00:51:47,538
You need to raise your standards for men.

938
00:51:47,538 --> 00:51:49,005
Don't just focus on their looks.

939
00:51:49,005 --> 00:51:51,838
Huh? I don't just focus on their looks.

940
00:51:51,838 --> 00:51:54,305
Masculinity, manliness,

941
00:51:54,305 --> 00:51:56,072
things like that...

942
00:51:56,072 --> 00:51:57,105
A macho man?

943
00:51:57,105 --> 00:51:58,138
No.

944
00:51:58,138 --> 00:52:00,938
Not that extreme.

945
00:52:00,938 --> 00:52:04,305
Whatever. I'm done dating men.

946
00:52:04,305 --> 00:52:05,338
Don't believe you.

947
00:52:05,338 --> 00:52:07,505
You said the exact same thing last month.

948
00:52:07,505 --> 00:52:09,972
I'm serious.

949
00:52:09,972 --> 00:52:11,672
Here.

950
00:52:30,405 --> 00:52:31,653
[Hangover Remedy]

951
00:52:59,005 --> 00:53:00,772
Darn it.

952
00:53:00,772 --> 00:53:02,292
What?

953
00:53:02,292 --> 00:53:03,805
What?

954
00:53:06,072 --> 00:53:08,105
- I think I'm drunk.
- Huh?

955
00:53:08,738 --> 00:53:11,438
I'm drunk. Really drunk.

956
00:53:11,438 --> 00:53:13,138
Where are you going?

957
00:53:15,172 --> 00:53:17,105
[Busy?]

958
00:53:22,181 --> 00:53:23,205
[Busy?]

959
00:53:24,837 --> 00:53:26,341
[My Hangover Remedy]

960
00:53:32,138 --> 00:53:33,605
[Finding the Next Try Beer]

961
00:53:33,605 --> 00:53:36,505
The next Try Beer.

962
00:53:36,505 --> 00:53:38,238
Okay.

963
00:53:39,072 --> 00:53:41,472
How about we all grab a beer tonight?

964
00:53:42,205 --> 00:53:44,772
Aw, you all heard me.
Are you pretending you didn't?

965
00:53:44,772 --> 00:53:46,738
Don't get scolded by your wife again.

966
00:53:46,738 --> 00:53:48,538
Go home early.

967
00:53:48,538 --> 00:53:50,372
Right, your little bunnies

968
00:53:50,372 --> 00:53:53,372
are waiting for you at home, Manager Nah.

969
00:53:53,372 --> 00:53:55,472
But why beer all of a sudden?
What's special today?

970
00:53:55,472 --> 00:53:56,872
No, no. Not a team dinner.

971
00:53:56,872 --> 00:53:59,738
Market research for the competition.

972
00:53:59,738 --> 00:54:01,105
Come on.

973
00:54:01,105 --> 00:54:03,105
Isn't it lonely preparing
for the competition alone?

974
00:54:03,105 --> 00:54:05,605
Instead, how about we all go for it

975
00:54:05,605 --> 00:54:06,972
together as a team?

976
00:54:06,972 --> 00:54:09,738
Last time, when we suggested everyone
try individually, didn't you say it was fine?

977
00:54:09,738 --> 00:54:12,338
Assistant Manager Choi, I'm just like a reed.

978
00:54:12,338 --> 00:54:14,205
My mind changes all the time.

979
00:54:14,205 --> 00:54:15,372
Alright, last chance.

980
00:54:15,372 --> 00:54:17,905
Anyone want to join me? Hands up!

981
00:54:21,338 --> 00:54:23,005
Really, no one? Nice!

982
00:54:23,005 --> 00:54:24,438
I'll just team up with another department.

983
00:54:24,438 --> 00:54:26,072
Really? You'll regret missing
this chance with me.

984
00:54:26,072 --> 00:54:27,872
Try ask Manager Jang.

985
00:54:27,872 --> 00:54:29,538
- Manager Jang?
- She's not here. You never know.

986
00:54:29,538 --> 00:54:30,938
She might say yes.

987
00:54:30,938 --> 00:54:33,305
You think? No, Manager Jang
wouldn't want to team up with me.

988
00:54:33,305 --> 00:54:36,038
Why the sudden put-down? It doesn't suit you.

989
00:54:36,038 --> 00:54:37,705
Just ask her.

990
00:54:37,705 --> 00:54:40,505
Your styles are complete opposites.
That might actually create synergy.

991
00:54:40,505 --> 00:54:42,272
You think so?

992
00:54:42,272 --> 00:54:43,638
No. I'll do it alone.

993
00:54:43,638 --> 00:54:44,838
Shall I ask on your behalf?

994
00:54:44,838 --> 00:54:47,738
I think Manager Jang is considering
whether to do this as a team too.

995
00:54:47,738 --> 00:54:48,772
Really?

996
00:54:48,772 --> 00:54:49,938
Well, I'm grateful.

997
00:54:49,938 --> 00:54:51,138
Se Hyeon, let's do it together.

998
00:54:51,138 --> 00:54:54,738
Let's work properly with people
whose minds are aligned.

999
00:54:55,772 --> 00:54:56,872
Jealous?

1000
00:54:56,872 --> 00:54:58,138
He's excited. Just excited.

1001
00:54:58,138 --> 00:54:59,872
Looks like they fought today.

1002
00:55:01,005 --> 00:55:02,638
Yes.

1003
00:55:02,638 --> 00:55:06,738
Let's just reinforce the financial
structure sheet from last time.

1004
00:55:06,738 --> 00:55:09,605
Please proceed at your discretion, Director.

1005
00:55:09,605 --> 00:55:12,389
The deadline is... just a moment.

1006
00:55:12,389 --> 00:55:14,538
[To-do List]

1007
00:55:14,538 --> 00:55:15,838
[First Fetal Abnormality Screening (4:30 PM)]

1008
00:55:15,838 --> 00:55:18,072
Let's set it for tomorrow afternoon.

1009
00:55:18,072 --> 00:55:19,772
Okay.

1010
00:55:22,105 --> 00:55:23,838
It's today.

1011
00:55:28,638 --> 00:55:30,672
[Jang Hui Won]
Are you feeling okay?

1012
00:55:30,672 --> 00:55:33,438
I'll contact you after finishing
today's schedule.

1013
00:55:39,638 --> 00:55:40,672
Du Jun!

1014
00:55:40,672 --> 00:55:42,872
- What?
- The Chairman...

1015
00:55:48,538 --> 00:55:52,038
It appears sudden shock
or stress strained his heart.

1016
00:55:52,038 --> 00:55:53,972
He's over the hump with a quick fix,

1017
00:55:53,972 --> 00:55:56,438
but his heart function was
already significantly weakened.

1018
00:55:56,438 --> 00:56:00,838
If this happens again,
it could be very dangerous.

1019
00:56:02,872 --> 00:56:05,438
What happened? He collapsed suddenly?

1020
00:56:05,438 --> 00:56:07,005
Du Jun.

1021
00:56:07,005 --> 00:56:08,105
I don't know.

1022
00:56:08,105 --> 00:56:12,705
He doesn't tell me who he meets

1023
00:56:12,705 --> 00:56:13,905
or what he does these days.

1024
00:56:13,905 --> 00:56:15,838
I'll try to find out.

1025
00:56:15,838 --> 00:56:18,138
Stay with Madam.

1026
00:56:21,505 --> 00:56:23,638
Honey.

1027
00:56:24,672 --> 00:56:27,338
Dear.

1028
00:56:33,072 --> 00:56:35,905
Huh? Hui Won?

1029
00:56:36,938 --> 00:56:38,725
[OB-GYN]

1030
00:56:46,905 --> 00:56:50,072
Ah, today's the day.

1031
00:56:52,005 --> 00:56:54,205
But why is she alone?

1032
00:57:12,205 --> 00:57:15,138
[President Kang Du Jun]

1033
00:57:15,138 --> 00:57:17,272
Sorry, something urgent came up.

1034
00:57:17,272 --> 00:57:19,272
Let's go to the hospital together next time.

1035
00:57:19,272 --> 00:57:23,605
What? He promised
he wouldn't let me go alone.

1036
00:57:25,038 --> 00:57:27,872
He's busy. It can't be helped.

1037
00:57:34,038 --> 00:57:35,738
Min Uk.

1038
00:57:36,472 --> 00:57:39,938
I saw you going in alone while passing by.

1039
00:57:39,938 --> 00:57:42,538
Didn't you say it was
an important test today?

1040
00:57:42,538 --> 00:57:45,472
Yeah, but I'm fine alone.

1041
00:57:45,472 --> 00:57:46,505
Don't worry.

1042
00:57:46,505 --> 00:57:49,272
I'll stay until your results come out.

1043
00:57:50,138 --> 00:57:52,005
Is it alright with you?

1044
00:57:52,005 --> 00:57:54,085
Sure.

1045
00:57:54,085 --> 00:57:55,772
Oh.

1046
00:57:56,581 --> 00:57:57,838
I looked it up,

1047
00:57:57,838 --> 00:58:00,305
and apparently drinking chocolate milk
before the fetal movement test

1048
00:58:00,305 --> 00:58:01,638
makes it easier.

1049
00:58:01,638 --> 00:58:06,238
Oh, you mean that sweet stuff
makes the baby more active?

1050
00:58:06,238 --> 00:58:08,005
Yeah.

1051
00:58:08,005 --> 00:58:11,538
It's not scientifically proven, apparently.

1052
00:58:12,372 --> 00:58:14,072
Really?

1053
00:58:14,938 --> 00:58:18,772
But perfect timing since I was craving sugar.

1054
00:58:18,772 --> 00:58:21,038
Such good timing.

1055
00:58:38,105 --> 00:58:40,438
Didn't you have an appointment?

1056
00:58:40,438 --> 00:58:41,705
I postponed it.

1057
00:58:41,705 --> 00:58:43,772
If it's important, you should go.

1058
00:58:43,772 --> 00:58:45,638
It's fine. I can stay here.

1059
00:58:45,638 --> 00:58:47,638
No, I need to stay until he's awake.

1060
00:58:47,638 --> 00:58:51,538
As his wife, I can watch over him right here.

1061
00:58:51,538 --> 00:58:54,972
But Du Jun, you have to keep
the promise you made.

1062
00:58:54,972 --> 00:58:58,438
I'll call you right away when Dad wakes up.

1063
00:59:05,372 --> 00:59:08,538
Your dad was snoring a little while ago.

1064
00:59:08,538 --> 00:59:10,938
See? He just fell asleep.

1065
00:59:34,672 --> 00:59:37,605
If you're still at the hospital,
I'm heading there now.

1066
00:59:38,372 --> 00:59:41,605
Ms. Jang Hui Won, please come
into the 3D ultrasound room.

1067
00:59:41,605 --> 00:59:42,638
Okay.

1068
00:59:42,638 --> 00:59:44,972
Guardian, please come in too.

1069
00:59:57,538 --> 00:59:59,238
There.

1070
01:00:04,338 --> 01:00:05,905
I'm hot, I am...

1071
01:00:05,905 --> 01:00:09,205
How can one night compete with fifteen years?

1072
01:00:09,205 --> 01:00:12,872
You only come to me
when you need help, don't you?

1073
01:00:12,872 --> 01:00:15,272
Who else would I ask for
a favor like this besides you?

1074
01:00:15,272 --> 01:00:16,805
Do you like Jang Hui Won?

1075
01:00:16,805 --> 01:00:20,038
I plan to confess to her seriously soon.

1076
01:00:21,093 --> 01:00:23,672
Give this to me.

1077
01:00:23,672 --> 01:00:25,405
Thanks.

1078
01:00:28,672 --> 01:00:29,938
It's really fine.

1079
01:00:29,938 --> 01:00:33,438
You can't catch a cold.
You should have dressed warmly.

1080
01:00:51,572 --> 01:00:54,605
You don't have to come. It's all over.

1081
01:01:15,705 --> 01:01:17,805
[Epilogue]

1082
01:01:17,805 --> 01:01:20,572
You had a rough day yesterday,

1083
01:01:20,572 --> 01:01:23,705
so clear your mind and get some proper rest.

1084
01:01:23,705 --> 01:01:26,672
Eat well even when I'm not there.

1085
01:01:26,672 --> 01:01:29,972
This is tonic, so take it 30 minutes
after meals, got it?

1086
01:01:29,972 --> 01:01:31,538
Got it.

1087
01:01:31,538 --> 01:01:32,572
Well, look at you.

1088
01:01:32,572 --> 01:01:33,838
You're smiling.

1089
01:01:33,838 --> 01:01:35,472
You get annoyed, then suddenly laugh,

1090
01:01:35,472 --> 01:01:37,872
get angry, then suddenly laugh,
then suddenly get annoyed...

1091
01:01:37,872 --> 01:01:42,305
You have quite a few
personalities hidden inside you, huh?

1092
01:01:50,038 --> 01:01:53,105
You finished the whole bowl.
You won't feel sick anymore. Sleep well.

1093
01:01:53,105 --> 01:01:54,972
Why are you peeking at my texts?

1094
01:01:54,972 --> 01:01:58,072
What? Did you eat samgyetang
with Manager Jang? Is that it?

1095
01:01:58,072 --> 01:01:59,938
- No, nothing like that.
- Nothing?

1096
01:01:59,938 --> 01:02:01,172
But it is, right?

1097
01:02:01,172 --> 01:02:03,738
Last time, you made a fuss
about Manager Jang being jealous.

1098
01:02:03,738 --> 01:02:04,938
Now it's samgyetang?

1099
01:02:04,938 --> 01:02:07,972
She said she doesn't take
just anyone to that samgyetang place.

1100
01:02:07,972 --> 01:02:10,872
But she took me there,
so I must be more than just anyone.

1101
01:02:10,872 --> 01:02:12,705
She just took you there to feed you

1102
01:02:12,705 --> 01:02:14,372
because you looked exhausted, right?

1103
01:02:14,372 --> 01:02:15,838
No! I'm telling you, it's not!

1104
01:02:15,838 --> 01:02:17,772
She said she'd even lend me
her shoulder for five minutes.

1105
01:02:17,772 --> 01:02:19,672
Will you do that if you're not close?

1106
01:02:19,672 --> 01:02:22,872
Yep, I could lend my shoulder
to a stranger all day long.

1107
01:02:22,872 --> 01:02:24,538
You're too easy, way too easy. Seriously.

1108
01:02:24,538 --> 01:02:26,538
And you shouldn't lend your shoulder.

1109
01:02:26,538 --> 01:02:27,572
You can't lend it.

1110
01:02:27,572 --> 01:02:30,938
Why? Because you don't have
any shoulders. None at all.

1111
01:02:32,005 --> 01:02:36,038
My shoulders are broader
than you think. This is no joke.

1112
01:02:36,038 --> 01:02:38,305
That is the funniest thing.

1113
01:02:38,305 --> 01:02:41,105
I'm so stressed out right now.

1114
01:02:41,105 --> 01:02:42,972
I think I need to take that tonic.

1115
01:02:42,972 --> 01:02:44,638
Take that. There are two.

1116
01:02:44,638 --> 01:02:47,738
It's tonic, one for your mom
and one for you. So give it to her.

1117
01:02:47,738 --> 01:02:50,272
Don't take it all by yourself.

1118
01:02:50,272 --> 01:02:51,702
- Really?
- And the accounting team

1119
01:02:51,702 --> 01:02:52,938
deposited your bonus yesterday.

1120
01:02:52,938 --> 01:02:54,872
Set up an alert for the transactions.

1121
01:02:54,872 --> 01:02:56,972
You don't even know how to do it,
even now. Like an old man, seriously.

1122
01:02:56,972 --> 01:02:57,972
President Kang Du Jun.

1123
01:02:57,972 --> 01:03:00,738
Once again, thank you so much.

1124
01:03:01,805 --> 01:03:03,938
Du Jun.

1125
01:03:03,938 --> 01:03:04,972
I love you.

1126
01:03:04,972 --> 01:03:07,105
Creepy.

1127
01:03:07,105 --> 01:03:09,005
Go home quickly.

1128
01:03:09,005 --> 01:03:11,072
That's how you show love!

1129
01:03:11,072 --> 01:03:12,472
Ah, that grumpy man.

1130
01:03:12,472 --> 01:03:15,038
Seriously, who even notices that?

1131
01:03:15,038 --> 01:03:16,772
Thanks.

1132
01:03:57,005 --> 01:04:00,605
It's fine. Plenty of pregnant women
go to the hospital alone.

1133
01:04:00,605 --> 01:04:03,005
Could she be hiding that they went together?

1134
01:04:03,005 --> 01:04:04,705
Read and ignored? He read it and ignored it?

1135
01:04:04,705 --> 01:04:08,072
I think the one caught in between
isn't me, but the President.

1136
01:04:08,072 --> 01:04:10,905
Whether it was one night or fifteen years,
I don't really care about that stuff.

1137
01:04:10,905 --> 01:04:11,905
[Min Uk]
Can you just

1138
01:04:11,905 --> 01:04:13,672
focus on me for now?

1139
01:04:13,672 --> 01:04:16,472
I hope the person you really need
by your side right now is me.

1140
01:04:16,472 --> 01:04:19,205
I thought I was naturally
the one you needed, Ms. Jang Hui Won.

1141
01:04:19,205 --> 01:04:22,038
But today, it suddenly occurred to me
that it might not be me.

1142
01:04:22,038 --> 01:04:23,705
I confessed to Hui Won.

1143
01:04:23,705 --> 01:04:25,872
And I'm confident I can handle it.
